== Introduction

This virtual lab demonstrates how to create a Docker container that runs VLC media player to play a local video file. 
This can be useful for testing media files in a containerized environment or for deploying a media kiosk application.

== Prerequisites

- Docker installed on your system.
- A video file named `video.mp4` in the same directory as the Dockerfile.

== Getting Started

Follow the instructions in the INSTALL file to set up and run the virtual lab.

== Services and Tools Used

- Docker: For containerization.
- VLC: For media playback.

